[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/dont"]
[Student "S"]
{You only have 8 HCP but with such a good 6-card suit you should interfere with a DONT bid. You double and partner surprises you by saying 2\H.

There is a reason partner didn't say 2\C (which you were going to pass). And the reason is that he figures you will be better off in his \Hs. Since you trust your partner you pass.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "N"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "N:AT6.K5.A952.AJ54 KQJ83.AT764.6.K8 9542.93.J83.QT62 7.QJ82.KQT74.973"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "4H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "N"]
1NT 2H pass 3H pass 4H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: E, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 0, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "bde999b3681b0c9f8c9dfad1442634dafda206c5bfbac811d2f34ef03d1ac42f"]
[Category "Competitive Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/dont"]
[Student "S"]
{Since partner has entered the bidding in the immediate seat he should have a pretty good hand, with 9+ cards in \Hs and \Ss.

Usually you are happy to settle for partscore after a DONT sequence, but with such an excellent fit for \Hs your hand is worth a raise.

So you bid 3\H and partner says 4\H.}

